<br>
Here's the scenario: You invite a mage because you can't do the raid without one. The mage wants to random roll on a piece of loot if it drops. Now, let's say there are no other mages that are willing to go. You can:<br>
<br>
a) Say no, and nobody gets loot at all. Not even your guild because you can't do the raid without said mage.<br>
b) Give the mage a shot at loot and have him/her roll against all the other casters in your guild. This way you get all the loot except a small chance of not getting one piece.<br>
<br>
If the mage is being considered for a guild invite, then he/she should abide by the loot rules. But if not, I see no reason to expect them to have to abide by them or to consider them a loot whore if they want a fair shot at a piece of loot. After all, they are providing you a much needed service. <p>Omicron Nae'blis<BR>
