<br>
I will say this again, it'll be a cold day in hell when I give loot to a first-timer over our veteran raiders.  Nobody is forced into raiding with anyone.<br>
<br>
As a side note, if we invite and out-of-guild person to a raid and a piece of loot or spell drops that none of us need/want, then you bet your ass we will allow the non-guildee to loot it if he/she so desires.  I am simply speaking of loot that our regular guildmates have shown interest in.  The same rule appplies to class-specific loot.  If you're a temp member and you're the only person representing your class, then of course you will get the loot.  <br>
<br>
